<HEADLINE>
MOE, 228 FOUNDATION TO HOST EXHIBITION FEB. 28
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, Feb. 27 (CNA) 02/27/07  21:20:47 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Education (MOE) and the 228 Incident Memorial
Foundation will host an exhibition to commemorate the 60th
anniversary of the 228 Incident from Feb. 28 at the newly
established National 228 Memorial Museum, an MOE official said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The official said the museum, located at the intersection of
Nanhai Road and Chuanchou Street in Taipei City, will open Feb.
28, which marks the 60th anniversary of the 228 Incident of 1947.
President Chen Shui-bian will preside over the museum's unveiling
and opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Education Minister Tu Cheng-sheng and the foundation's Board
Chairman Chen Chin- huang introduced the exhibition's themes,
topics and content at a press conference and the official said
the exhibition, planned by the National Museum of History, will
include topics such as facing the truth of 228, forgiving,
rethinking, breaking and being reborn."
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is designed to present historical materials,
photos and audio recordings relating to the incident, and also to
introduce the future vision of the museum, the official said.
</P>
